19/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament supported, in principle, the stationing of US military bases in the country, in a declaration approved Thursday (18 December). The document was backed by 200 of the 240 deputies present. It expressed parliament's support for ongoing consultations between US and Bulgarian authorities on the possible relocation of bases to Southeast Europe. The declaration also read that the government was to regularly brief parliament on the progress of the talks, and confirmed Bulgaria's foreign policy priority of expanding its strategic partnership with Washington. (Trud, Sega - 19/12/03; BTA, BNT, bTV - 18/12/03)
